?','-n\n--newest',478,NULL),(4,'What pgrep option selects only the oldest (least recently started) of the matching processes?','-o\n--oldest',479,NULL),(4,'What pgrep option sets the string used to delimit each process ID in the output? and what is the default delimiter?','-d <delim>\n--delimiter <delim>\n\nDefault: newline (\n)',480,NULL),(4,'What pgrep option supresses normal output, and instead prints a count of matching processes?','-c\n--count',481,NULL),(4,'What priority value is set by the nice command if no priority value is supplied? What priority value is the default when nice is not used at all?','10\n\n0',482,NULL),(4,'What ps option displays all of the processes on the system?','-A\n-e',483,NULL),(4,'What ps option displays processes owned by a particular user?','-u <user>\nU <user>\n--user <user>\n\nNote: <user> may be a username or user ID',484,NULL),(4,'What ps option displays the processes owned by the user running ps?','x',485,NULL),(4,'What ps option expands the information provided in the ps output?','-f, -l\nj, l, u, v',486,NULL),(4,'What ps option groups processes and uses indentation to show the hierarchical relationships between processes?','-H\n-f\n--forest',487,NULL),(4,'What ps option prevents truncating of output beyond 80 characters in width?','-w\nw',488,NULL),(4,'What ps option summarizes common ps options?','--help',489,NULL),(4,'What renice option can be used to explicity set the priority value paramater?','-n <priority>\n--priority <priority>\n\nNote: This option, if used, must be used as the first argument.',490,NULL),(4,'What renice option enables matches by process group ID (pgrp / pgid)?','-g <pgid>\n--pgrp <pgid>',491,NULL),(4,'What renice option enables matches by process IDs (PIDs)?','-p <pid>\n--pid <pid>',492,NULL),(4,'What renice option enables matches by username or user ID (UID)?','-u <name|UID>\n--user <name|UID>',493,NULL),(4,'What search pattern value is supported by pgrep?','An extendend REGEXP',494,NULL),(4,'What three ways are there to specify a priority value in the nice command?','nice -<value>\nnice -n <value>\nnice --adjustment=<value>',495,NULL),(4,'What top command changes a process\'s priority (i.e. renice) after prompting for its PID and a new priority value? What values are supported? What is the default value?','r\n\n-20 to 19\n\n0',496,NULL),(4,'What top command displays help information?','h\n?',497,NULL),(4,'What top command kills a process after prompting for its PID?','k',498,NULL),(4,'What top command prompts for a new update rate in seconds?','s',499,NULL),(4,'What top command quits top?','q',500,NULL),(4,'What top command sorts by CPU usage?','P',501,NULL),(4,'What top command sorts by memory usage?','M',502,NULL),(4,'What top option changes the update interval in seconds? and what is the default value?','-d <seconds>\n\nDefault: 5 seconds',503,NULL),(4,'What top option displays a specific number of updates before quitting?','-n <num>',504,NULL),(4,'What top option enables batch mode? and what does this mode do?','-b\n\nPrevents normal screen-update commands. Useful for logging CPU use to a file.',505,NULL),(4,'What top option monitors a specific proccess by PID? and how many processes can be monitored simultaneously?','-p <pid>\n\nUp to 20 PIDs can be monitored by applying the same option with a unique PID per -p flag.',506,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays all available information?','-a\n--all',507,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays information about the machine?','-m\n--machine\n\nNote: the output is generally a CPU code, such as x86_64 or i386, etc.',508,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays the actual kernel version number?','-r\n--kernel-release',509,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays the kernel name?','-s\n--kernel-name\n\nNote: The value returned is typically \'Linux\' on a Linux system.',510,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays the kernel version?','-v\n--kernel-version',511,NULL),(4,'What uname option displays the system\'s node name / netwo